##15-year-old boy carries 15,000 masks from foreign countries

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

By Lee Ching and Han Xiaorong, _ thepaper.cn _

With 15,000 masks and no one willing to "risk" , the 15-year-old returned home alone with five heavy suitcases from Indonesia.

Recently, Zhao Junyan, a student in Class 8(2) of Shanghai's privately-run New Huangpu Experimental School, "caught fire. " Teachers, students, friends and relatives, as well as Internet users have praised him for this little anti-epidemic Hero: "since ancient times, " "good children, " "role models" ... 

"when the country is in trouble, everyone is responsible! We just did what ordinary Chinese should do, " Zhao and her family told the www.thepaper.cn  

A mask collected by Zhao Junyan from Indonesia. Images courtesy of Huangpu District, Shanghai

Volunteered to be a "mask porter. "

January winter vacation, in Jakarta, Indonesia, work and live Uncle Travel and Europe, invited Zhao Junyan to local vacation.

On January 18, Zhao was flying from Shanghai to Jakarta to begin his winter vacation. Within days of their arrival, however, news of a new domestic outbreak of pneumonia spread to their home town of Cangnan County, Wenzhou.

As an overseas Chinese living abroad, you Hezhou's heart is tied to his motherland and hometown. In order to snap up masks in the first place, he put down his original foreign trade business, on January 23rd, more than 20,000 surgical masks were purchased in just two days, with staff working as fast as possible to collect emergency medical masks from Sumatra, Java, Sulawesi, Borneo and other islands, to the Cangnan County People's Hospital in Wenzhou.

When the masks were ready to be bought, they had a problem: because shipping was so expensive, it was better for someone to fly home, but no one there was willing to do the heavy lifting in China at a time when the epidemic was so severe.

Is at a loss, Zhao Junyan put forward: "Uncle, let me come. I fly back to China. "

My uncle was hesitant to travel to Hezhou, when the epidemic situation in the country was getting worse and the start of school was postponed. I had been too busy collecting masks to take my nephew to play.

Zhao's mother also changed the time of her flight because of the delayed start of school, hoping the child would stay longer in Jakarta and return home after February 10.

Zhao Junyan and his mother: "I have been a middle school students, I am Chinese, this difficult time, I do my best for the country to do something for home, it is incumbent upon me. "

You Xiaomin, the mother, was impressed by her son. Although she was a little worried, she believed more in the little man. On February 2, the Indonesian government issued a notice to close all flights to and from China starting at 12 o'clock on February 5. The time was urgent, you Xiaomin quickly helped his son to get back the ticket, finally grabbed a February 323:00 air ticket, only to learn later that this is now Indonesia to China's last flight.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhao Junyan and uncle

Five suitcases, 15,000 masks

In order to transport as many masks as possible back to China, Zhao tore off the mask packaging to reduce the space occupied, 15,000 masks were crammed into five 24-inch suitcases. Five suitcases was the maximum load he could bear.

In uncle's help, Zhao Jun Yan checked the five 24-inch luggage, alone on the return flight.

At 7 a.m. on February 4, Zhao arrived at the Shanghai Pudong International Airport. When he went through the customs, shy, he found some kind people to help him out of the customs. He was going to guard the suitcase, and then he was going to call the courier company, and the courier would come and pick up the goods. But the staff told him to bring the goods to the airport by himself. He pulled out his cell phone and checked his location. He was more than 500 meters from his destination.

In the face of five big boxes, Zhao Junyan very difficult... finally, he found two carts, five boxes on the car, a push up two carts, but always a box is not obedient, keep falling. He could only push one for a while, then go back to push another... so, 500 meters walk for half an hour, five suitcases finally successfully moved to the airport outside.

Zhao first contacted express, two hours later, the goods finally headed to their hometown of Cangnan County.

A suitcase full of masks

A teacher at the new Huangpu Experimental School told The Paper that Zhao Junyan is the monitor of Class 8(2) at the school. He is a good student with good grades and is always ready to help others. He is trusted by his friends. He has always been brave and responsible, this time from overseas "human meat" back to the mask, is also expected. At an unusual time, a 15-year-old Shanghai boy staged a "Riding Alone for Thousands of Miles, " and the story of Dazhi and Dayong became good material for the school to carry out responsible education. The school has spread Zhao Junyan's story among the students, hope that more students to his example, the heart of the motherland, the courage to assume.
